 \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249754493796806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1092, \"end\": 1100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9079136523269187e-13, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"varied venues\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1064}, {\"ngram\": \"Salon\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s list\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1145}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1159}, {\"ngram\": \"this summer's Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1209}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the first time in the history of the Olympic Summer Games, the Opening Ceremony will take place outside of a stadium.\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1298, \"end\": 1314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9999999992342055, \"rank\": 7.512599720063169e-10, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1249}, {\"ngram\": \"the history\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1264}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Summer Games\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1292}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1330}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1351}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the ceremony will be waterborne across nearly four miles of Paris\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 famous Seine River, ushering in athletes on a parade of boats designated to reflect each respective country.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1539, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1374}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly four miles\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1418}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 famous Seine River\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1449}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1471}, {\"ngram\": \"a parade\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1483}, {\"ngram\": \"boats\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"each respective country\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1538}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to theOlympics' official website,the boats will be fitted with cameras to provide fans watching online and via television with a close-up view of the athletes.\\u00c2 \\u00c2 Starting at 7:30 p.m. CET (10:30 a.m. PST and 1:30 p.m. EST), the procession will depart from the Austerlitz Bridge near the Jardin des Plantes and will end in front of the Trocad\\u00c3\\u00a9ro Gardens, where the remaining elements of the ceremony will unfold.\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Austerlitz Bridge\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theOlympics' official website\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1582}, {\"ngram\": \"the boats\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"cameras\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1620}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 1632, \"to\": 1636}, {\"ngram\": \"television\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1671}, {\"ngram\": \"a close-up view\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1692}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1708}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2 \\u00c2\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1712}, {\"ngram\": \"7:30 p.m.\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"CET\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"10:30 a.m. PST\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1754}, {\"ngram\": \"1:30 p.m.\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1768}, {\"ngram\": \"EST\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"the procession\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1789}, {\"ngram\": \"the Jardin des Plantes\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1856}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1878}, {\"ngram\": \"the Trocad\\u00c3\\u00a9ro Gardens\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1904}, {\"ngram\": \"the remaining elements\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 1934}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 1950}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2 SuperstarsCeline DionandLady Gagaare reportedly slated to perform aduetrendition of\\u00c2 \\u00c3\\u0089dith Piaf\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s \\\"La Vie en Rose\\\" at the opening ceremony, marking Dion's first public performance since she was forced to stop touring after revealing to the world that she had been diagnosed with Stiff Person Syndrome (SPS), a rare autoimmune neurological disorder.\\u00c2 \\u00c2 The Paris 2024 Opening Ceremony will be the largest in Olympic history, as noted by the official site.\", \"from\": 1967, \"to\": 2429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2275, \"end\": 2278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9996636974192467, \"rank\": 0.0003363673518471088, \"text\": \"SPS\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2 SuperstarsCeline DionandLady Gagaare\", \"from\": 1967, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"aduetrendition of\\u00c2\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2053}, {\"ngram\": \"La Vie\", \"from\": 2071, \"to\": 2077}, {\"ngram\": \"Rose\", \"from\": 2081, \"to\": 2085}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2110}, {\"ngram\": \"Dion's first public performance\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2151}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2217}, {\"ngram\": \"Stiff Person Syndrome\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2272}, {\"ngram\":