ahupo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099o\", \"from\": 5591, \"to\": 5602}, {\"ngram\": \"a village\", \"from\": 5604, \"to\": 5613}, {\"ngram\": \"the southeastern coast\", \"from\": 5618, \"to\": 5640}, {\"ngram\": \"French Polynesia\", \"from\": 5654, \"to\": 5670}, {\"ngram\": \"the middle\", \"from\": 5674, \"to\": 5684}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pacific Ocean\", \"from\": 5688, \"to\": 5705}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 9,800 miles away from Paris, Teahupo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099o is the most distant venue from a host city in Games\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 history,according to Washington Post.\", \"from\": 5707, \"to\": 5843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5732, \"end\": 5737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249754493796806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5827, \"end\": 5837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"score\": 0.9992706505647289, \"rank\": 0.0007298752584681685, \"text\": \"Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Teahupo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099o\", \"from\": 5739, \"to\": 5750}, {\"ngram\": \"the most distant venue\", \"from\": 5754, \"to\": 5776}, {\"ngram\": \"a host city\", \"from\": 5782, \"to\": 5793}, {\"ngram\": \"Games\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 history\", \"from\": 5797, \"to\": 5813}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2 Known as\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe End of the Road,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009dTeahupo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099o is infamous for its idyllic surfing conditions, notoriously heavy waves and shallow shelf of coral, making it a deeply challenging surf venue.\", \"from\": 5845, \"to\": 6036, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Road\", \"from\": 5869, \"to\": 5877}, {\"ngram